rls_vsn.rls_vsn_ds: This release is a test for Release Version

appl_resrce.appl_ds: Provide AR billing functionality for CCSG, LAIDC, and OPEN Card Products

attr_resrce.attr_def: Service Establishment Number is a unique identifier for a merchant within American Express.
Grandfather Date (need further details)

Placed Account Payment Transaction Type Indicator specifies whether the incoming transaction is a payment from an outside collection agency, a direct payment from the placed card holder, an NSF transaction for a placed card holder.
Major Industry Code is a Standard Industry Code used to classify the industry of a service establishment.
FILLER
Transaction Transfer Code identifies how the transaction for an account that has been transferred is to be processed.
Transaction Date is the date on which the transaction occurred.
JETS Category Code is a 6-digit identifier used to specify a GL account and offset for posting to the general ledger system.
ATM Cash Advance Indicator specifies whether or not the transaction is an automated teller cash advance.
Authorization Code is a numerical code assigned to the vendor that authorizes the transaction.
Original Transaction Reference Number is an identifier for the transaction generated at the originator.
Securitization Included Date is the date on which securitization was included on the card holder account.
Product Code is an identifier for the card product involved in the transaction. A product is the assignment of parameters for items in the cardholder system.

Credit Debit Type Code specifies whether or not a transaction is positive (Debit) or negative (Credit). A debit transaction increases the balances in an account, and a credit transaction decreases the balances in an account.
Strategy Code 1 identifies the first branch of a strategy, and is composed of strategy type, portfolio ID, criteria group, and action group.
Representative Last Update Identifier is the id of the representative who made the last update to an entity.
Business Date identifies the date associated with the card member transaction.
Business Card Transaction Indicator identifies whether a transaction must be a business card transaction.
Sub Product Code 4 contains the code for the fourth user defined sub-product level.
Statement Day Date is exact day of the month on which the account was cycled.
Sub Product Code 3 contains the code for the third user defined sub-product level.
Sub Transaction Indicator (need further details)
General Ledger Master File Field identifies the master file field values (Card Member and merchant) that are to be accumulated in the specified GL account number.
Code Product Line Type identifies the product line type associated with this transaction.

General Ledger Entry Accumulation Code indicates whether or not GL entries for an owner id should be made individually or combined with other owner ids to make an accumulated entry to the specified GL account.
Merchant Category Code is a four-digit number listed in ISO 18245 for retail financial services, and is used to classify the business by the type of goods or services it provides.
Alternate Transaction Amount Code identifies the intent and purpose of the alternate transaction amount.
Charge Off Date is the date on which an account was assigned to charge off status.
Trust Indicator specifies if the account is part of one or more trusts.
Foreign Currency Description Length Number identifies the length of the foreign currency data received on a transaction.
General Ledger Institution Number is a system assigned number that identifies the institution that is adding, changing, or browsing the general ledger parameter file.
JETS Sub Category Code is a 6-digit identifier used to refine the mapping of a JETS category to a Triumph Transaction Code for the general ledger system.
Transfer To Account Number is the account number of the newly created account. This is the account number to which the transfer occurred.
General Ledger Cost Center Number identifies a unit of activity for which monetary activity is accumulated.
Transfer From Account Number is the account number of the previous account from which this account was originally created. This is the account number from which the transfer occurred.
Business Function Purchase Code identifies the business function associated with the purchase transaction.
Transaction Link Identifier provides a connection between multiple transactions, for example an originating cash transaction and its associated fee transaction.
Transaction Amount is the numerical amount associated with the specific transaction.
Securitization Included Indicator identifies if securitization has been used against card holder accounts.
Transaction Description is the primary description line associated with the transaction.
Vendor Number is an alphanumeric identifier used to uniquely specify a vendor.
Statement Month Date identifies the month on which the account was cycled.
Transaction City Name is the name of the city or town where transaction took place.

Transaction Code is assigned to uniquely describe the type of transaction processed by Triumph (Purchase, Cash Advance, Payment, etc.) which enables transaction amounts to be posted to the correct GL accounts.
General Ledger Account Number identifies the account maintained on the client or processor's general ledger system to accumulate financial data.
Merchant Currency Amount is the undecimalized transaction amount in settlement currency, right justified with leading zeros.
Demand Deposit Account Associated Number 4 (need further details)
Country Source Code is the standard 3-character code identifying the country where the transaction took place.
Authorization Code 1 (need further details)
Other Associated Number contains an identifier associated with a client/customer maintained on the Client Service System.
Address Postal Code is the postal code of the billing address for the account, including the 5-digit destination post office delivery area + 4-digit geographic segment qualifier.
Securitization Identifier specifies the securitization id used against card holder accounts.
Promotional XXD Transaction Add Timestamp is the timestamp when the promotional XXD transaction was added to the database.
Promotional Balance Indicator specifies whether or not a promotional program has been set up and is being used by the account.
Merchant Card Member Client Code specifies whether the rule is for a merchant, Card Member, or a client.

General Ledger Transaction Code is assigned to uniquely describe the type of transaction processed by Triumph (Purchase, Cash Advance, Payment, etc.) which enables transaction amounts to be posted to the correct GL accounts.
Account Cycle Day Code is the billing day code for the next cycle date on the account.
Stock Keeping Unit Number is an alphanumeric code that identifies a product for the purpose of tracking inventory.
Settlement Currency Exponent Code indicates the position of the decimal point in the transaction amount.
A code that identifies the AR platform from which the record was sourced: C = Corporate, R = CRP, T = Triumph, O = Optima, G = Globestar, M = MNS.
Posted Date is the date that the transaction was posted to the general ledger.
Strategy Code 2 identifies the second branch of a strategy, and is composed of strategy type, portfolio ID, criteria group, and action group.
Reversal Reason Code identifies the reason why a reversal was performed.
Time Added Load Timestamp (need further details)
Transaction Card Member Billing Currency Code is the ISO numeric destination currency code transmitted by FINCAP.
Offer Terms Code specifies a promotional offer and a defined set of terms. It is added to the transaction during the qualification process.
Card Member Account Number is the unique id associated with a customer account in the Triumph system.
Merchant Country Currency Code is the ISO numeric currency code associated with the merchant's country code.
International Transaction Indicator identifies if the transaction is international, and is used to determine if a transaction qualifies for a particular interchange or promotional balance.
Player Account Number is a code which represents the ownership hierarchy for the card product, e.g. Charge, Lending, OPEN Charge, OPEN Lending.
Reference Message Number is used to identify a reference number for non-fatal, non-error messages.

Card Number (aka Plastic Card Number) is the number embossed on the card assigned to each card member associated with an account. This number is composed of an issuer identification number, individual account identification, and an accompanying check digit.
Transaction State Code is a standard 2-character state abbreviation where the transaction took place.
Securitization Type Code identifies the type of securitization which is used against card holder accounts.
Payment Type Code identifies the specific type of a payment transaction (e.g. paid in full, paid minimum due, paid only revolve balance).
Transaction Last Update Timestamp is the date and time of the last update to the database information.
Trust Identifier Code is the monitoring trust associated with a particular securitization id.
Posted Date Indicator specifies if the transaction is a Select And Pay Later transaction.
Check Number (need further details)
Transfer Statement Code identifies the decoded description that is to be printed on the Card Member statement for internally generated transactions (e.g. fees, insurance premiums).
Charge Off Class Code describes the reason an account was charged off (e.g. bankruptcy, deceased, fraud).
JETS Source Identifier Code is a 7-character identifier for a file that is passed to JETS.
Network Indicator specifies if the transaction is part of the ATM network.
Foreign Currency Description (need further details)
First Usage Draft Indicator specifies if this is the first use transaction for the card.
General Ledger Application Code identifies the processing application associated with the GL owner id.
Details Record Code is a code used to identify a record type as a detail record.
Alternate Transaction Amount represents a transaction amount that is different, yet associated with the base transaction amount.
Sub Industry Code is a Standard Industry Code used to classify the sub-industry of a service establishment.
Strategy Code 4 identifies the fourth branch of a strategy, and is composed of strategy type, portfolio ID, criteria group, and action group.
Card Member Account Terminal Indicator (need further details)
Transaction Override Code indicates whether or not the transaction text has been overridden by a Customer Service Representative.

Initial Arrangement Product Identification Code identifies an occurrence of the product entity. Card Configuration and Product Family codes can be up to 3 characters, while Initial Arrangement and Feature codes will be 6 characters.
Transaction Added Time is the date and time assigned when the record was added to the database.
Strategy Code 3 identifies the third branch of a strategy, and is composed of strategy type, portfolio ID, criteria group, and action group.
Sub Product Code 1 contains the code for the first user defined sub-product level.
Statement Year Date identifies the year on which the account was cycled.
Reclassification Charge Off Code contains the previous and current charge off code for a charge off reclassification.

Trailer Record Code is a code used to identify a record type as a trailer record.
